y%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETaking%20plus-ones%20on%20work%20trips%20is%20part%20of%20the%20growing%20blended%20travel%20trend%2C%20also%20known%20in%20the%20industry%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbleisure-travel-meaning-trend-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebleisure%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20business%20and%20leisure.%20It's%20when%20work%20travelers%20also%20throw%20some%20leisure%20into%20the%20mix%2C%20either%20throughout%20their%20trip%20or%20by%20tagging%20on%20some%20extra%2C%20non-work%20days%20on%20either%20end.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trend%20is%20especially%20enticing%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-pivot-college-degrees-work-blue-collar-jobs-trades-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGen%20Z%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20have%20a%20greater%20focus%20on%20work-life%20balance%20than%20older%20generations%2C%20according%20to%20a%20recent%20YouGov%20survey%20of%20over%2012%2C000%20people%20commissioned%20by%20Crowne%20Plaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20found%2074%25%20of%20respondents%20would%20invite%20a%20family%20member%20or%20friend%20on%20a%20work%20trip%2C%20with%20Gen%20Z%20and%20millennials%20being%20the%20most%20likely%20to%20do%20so.%20Nearly%20one%20in%20five%20respondents%20said%20they'd%20brought%20a%20plus-one%20on%20a%20work%20trip%20without%20telling%20their%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJean%20Twenge%2C%20a%20psychologist%20and%20the%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BGenerations%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20book%20about%20how%20Americans%20differ%20by%20generation%2C%20said%20Gen%20Z's%20approach%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-work-life-balance-advice-boss-lessons-job-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ework-life%20balance%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20be%20part%20of%20the%20reason%20they're%20more%20likely%20to%20bring%20a%20plus-one%20on%20a%20work%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20want%20their%20work%20to%20be%20their%20whole%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20could%20also%20be%20because%20they%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20responsibilities%20like%20children%20that%20would%20require%20their%20partner%20to%20stay%20home%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20why%20they%20might%20feel%20uncomfortable%20talking%20to%20their%20boss%20about%20bringing%20a%20plus-one%2C%20Twenge%20said%20it%20could%20be%20because%20they%20are%20relatively%20new%20to%20the%20workforce%20or%20their%20company%2C%20and%20they're%20just%20not%20sure%20if%20it%20would%20be%20okay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsc%2Fhow-to-enhance-business-trips-with-personal-growth%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eblended%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20bringing%20a%20plus-one%20on%20a%20work%20trip%20is%20encouraged%20by%20employers%2C%20said%20Ginger%20Taggart%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20brand%20management%20for%20global%20premium%20brands%20at%20IHG%20Hotels%20%26amp%3B%20Resorts%2C%20which%20owns%20Crowne%20Plaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20IHG%20has%20heard%20from%20its%20partners%20that%20bringing%20a%20plus-one%20on%20a%20work%20trip%20is%20no%20longer%20a%20%26quot%3Bdirty%20little%20secret.%26quot%3B%20In%20fact%2C%20some%20employers%20are%20actively%20looking%20to%20plan%20work%20trips%20that%20make%20blended%20travel%2C%20including%20with%20a%20guest%2C%20more%20enjoyable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20enables%20all%20of%20their%20workforce%20and%20their%20employees%20to%20benefit%20from%20the%20productivity%20of%20their%20business%20demands%2C%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%20having%20their%20life%20enriched%2C%26quot%3B%20Taggart%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20adding%20that%20employees%20say%20bringing%20a%20loved%20one%20on%20a%20work%20trip%20helps%20reduce%20their%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephan%20Meier%2C%20a%20professor%20and%20chair%20of%20the%20Management%20Division%20at%20Columbia%20Business%20School%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20it%20should%20be%20the%20employer's%20responsibility%20to%20ensure%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fturning-work-trips-into-vacations-according-to-frequent-traveler%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eexpectations%20on%20business%20trips%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20clear.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20it%20could%20be%20the%20case%20that%20employees%20are%20expected%20to%20work%209-to-5%20and%20then%20have%20the%20night%20to%20themselves%2C%20in%20which%20case%20their%20boss%20might%20not%20mind%20if%20a%20partner%20tags%20along.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20cases%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20age%20of%20remote%20work%2C%20the%20employees%20may%20be%20expected%20to%20participate%20in%20team%20dinners%20or%20other%20bonding%20activities%20in%20the%20evenings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEither%20way%20is%20acceptable%2C%20Meier%20said%2C%20but%20it's%20important%20that%20those%20expectations%20are%20clearly%20set%20and%20communicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20knows%20then%20what%20the%20rules%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20no%20hiding%20in%20the%20lobby%20or%20pretending%20we%20don't%20know%20each%20other%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20somebody%20else%20doesn't%20see%20that%20I'm%20together%20with%20my%20significant%20other.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%20about%20bringing%20a%20plus-one%20on%20a%20work%20trip%20or%20business%20travel%20in%20general%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Akvlamis%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ekvlamis%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-bringing-plus-one-work-trips-not-telling-boss-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1748261761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%