0That%20would%20be%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20turnover%20in%20data%20going%20back%20to%202001.%20The%20average%20over%20the%20same%20period%20is%2011.3%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20three%20months%20of%20the%20year%2C%20a%20record%20646%20US%20CEOs%20left%20their%20roles%2C%20according%20to%20Challenger%2C%20Gray%20%26amp%3B%20Christmas.%20That%20followed%20a%20busy%202024%2C%20when%20the%20number%20of%20departing%20chiefs%20rose%20to%20the%20highest%20annual%20level%20since%20the%20staffing%20and%20coaching%20firm%20began%20keeping%20tabs%20on%20CEO%20turnover%20in%202002.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222ad1c250-2531-423d-ae9a-3265973a4ad1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompanies%20want%20leaders%20with%20better%20ideas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECole%20said%20his%20firm%20is%20getting%20calls%20from%20boards%20and%20private%20equity%20firms%20looking%20to%20change%20directions%20with%20a%20new%20CEO.%20He%20said%20there's%20often%20a%20desire%20for%20visionary%20leaders%20who%20can%20think%20up%20the%20next%20great%20product%20or%20service%20to%20boost%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20like%2C%20'Holy%20sh%E2%80%94%2C%20we%20need%20some%20better%20ideas%20in%20the%20room%2C'%26quot%3B%20Cole%20said%20of%20boards%20and%20PE%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENormally%2C%20when%20corporate%20overseers%20want%20to%20make%20a%20change%20at%20the%20top%2C%20or%20are%20forced%20to%2C%20they%20can%20scan%20the%20org%20chart.%20Yet%2C%20he%20said%2C%20some%20up-and-comers%20have%20tired%20of%20riding%20the%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20upper%20management%20that's%20held%20on%20too%20long%2C%20and%20so%20what%20would%20have%20been%20your%20successor%20has%20now%20left%20the%20company%2C%26quot%3B%20Cole%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20he%20said%2C%20because%20many%20companies%20haven't%20invested%20in%20grooming%20the%20next%20generation%2C%20it's%20not%20always%20possible%20to%20simply%20poach%20a%20hotshot%20from%20a%20rival.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20musical%20chairs%20is%20broken%2C%26quot%3B%20Cole%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENevertheless%2C%20some%20companies%20are%20managing%20to%20woo%20outsiders.%20Among%20the%20companies%20that%20make%20up%20the%20broad%20S%26amp%3BP%201500%20index%2C%2044%25%20of%20new%20CEOs%20in%202024%20were%20external%20hires%2C%20according%20to%20data%20from%20the%20executive%20search%20firm%20Spencer%20Stuart.%20It's%20the%20largest%20share%20of%20outsiders%20since%20the%20firm%20began%20tracking%20the%20data%20in%202000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-ceo-retirement-surprise-succession-planning-berkshire-meeting-abel-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebiggest%20promotions%3C%2Fa%3E%20still%20come%20from%20within.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20Warren%20Buffett%20said%20that%20after%2055%20years%20running%20Berkshire%20Hathaway%2C%20he%20would%20step%20down%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20The%20conglomerate's%20board%20approved%20Buffett's%20chosen%20successor%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpromotion-move-up-things-to-consider-work-job-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGreg%20Abel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20is%20some%20three%20decades%20younger%20than%20the%2094-year-old%20Oracle%20of%20Omaha.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuffett's%20run%20is%20unmatched%20among%20heads%20of%20big%20US%20companies%20and%20far%20beyond%20what's%20typical.%20The%20average%20tenure%20of%20CEOs%20of%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20companies%20fell%20to%208.3%20years%20in%202024%20from%208.9%20years%20in%202023%2C%20Spencer%20Stuart%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKathy%20Gersch%2C%20chief%20commercial%20officer%20at%20the%20change-management%20firm%20Kotter%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20recent%20drops%20in%20CEO%20tenure%20signal%2C%20in%20part%2C%20that%20boards%20have%20less%20patience%20for%20missteps.%20That's%20one%20reason%2C%20she%20said%2C%20that%20directors%20need%20to%20understand%20the%20plans%20for%20developing%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c90504e5-483b-4af6-8b98-568f755853f7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EJob-hopping%20might%20not%20help%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20reason%20finding%20a%20CEO%20could%20be%20harder%20is%20that%20some%20workers%2C%20still%20early%20in%20their%20careers%2C%20don't%20necessarily%20want%20to%20grind%20it%20out%20at%20a%20single%20company%20with%20an%20eye%20toward%20climbing%20into%20the%20top%20job%2C%20Jason%20Schloetzer%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20at%20the%20McDonough%20School%20of%20Business%20at%20Georgetown%20University%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYears%20ago%2C%20he%20said%2C%20the%20goal%20might%20have%20been%20to%20complete%20a%20corporate%20management%20rotation%20%E2%80%94%20including%20turns%20in%20various%20departments%20and%20possibly%20foreign%20posts%20%E2%80%94%20to%20%26quot%3Breally%20understand%20the%20organization%20from%20top%20to%20bottom%20in%20order%20to%20matriculate%20up%20to%20the%20C-suite%2C%26quot%3B%20Schloetzer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Zers%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-gen-z-job-hopping-myth-switching-roles-boomers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echanging%20jobs%20less%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20prior%20generations%2C%20some%20business%20school%20grads%2C%20for%20example%2C%20often%20view%20career%20progression%20as%20jumping%20every%20two%20to%20three%20years%20among%20companies%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20mean%2C%20by%20the%20time%20they'd%20been%20in%20the%20workforce%20for%2015%20years%20after%20getting%20their%20MBA%2C%20these%20execs%20might%20have%20five%20or%20six%20companies%20on%20their%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%2C%20Schloetzer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20can%20be%20at%20odds%20with%20what%20some%20boards%20are%20seeking.%20Often%2C%20directors%20tap%20someone%20who%20might%20ha